{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-post-template-jsx","path":"/how-to-increase-travis-ci-timeout","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<p>There are different use cases where Travis jobs could raise the timeout error. Maybe you are trying to install a Python module that takes some time before installing the dependencies e.g:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"yml\"><pre class=\"language-yml\"><code class=\"language-yml\"><span class=\"token key atrule\">install</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span>\n    pip install torch</code></pre></div>\n<p>or you are running the Java project tests e.g</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"yml\"><pre class=\"language-yml\"><code class=\"language-yml\"><span class=\"token key atrule\">script</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span>\n    mvn package <span class=\"token punctuation\">-</span>Dtestng=test.xml</code></pre></div>\n<p>or pushing a new image to the Docker registry e.g</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"yml\"><pre class=\"language-yml\"><code class=\"language-yml\"><span class=\"token key atrule\">script</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span>\n    docker push $APPLICATION<span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span>$IMAGE_VERSION;</code></pre></div>\n<p>The default Travis job timeout is set to 10 min, so in some scenarios the above commands will fail with:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"text\"><pre class=\"language-text\"><code class=\"language-text\">Timeout (20 minutes) reached. Terminating &quot;...&quot;</code></pre></div>\n<p>To increase the <code class=\"language-text\">timeouts</code> travis ci offers a <a href=\"https://docs.travis-ci.com/user/common-build-problems/#build-times-out-because-no-output-was-received\">function</a> that will increase the build timeouts:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"yml\"><pre class=\"language-yml\"><code class=\"language-yml\"><span class=\"token key atrule\">install</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> travis_wait N mvn install</code></pre></div>\n<p>The <code class=\"language-text\">travis_wait n</code>  where the <code class=\"language-text\">n</code> is the minutes by which the waiting time is increased.</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Note: You must carefully use <code class=\"language-text\">travis_wait</code> since it can extend the build time when there could happen another issue.</p>\n</blockquote>","timeToRead":1,"excerpt":"There are different use cases where Travis jobs could raise the timeout error. Maybe you are trying to install a Python module that takes…","frontmatter":{"title":"How to increase Travis CI timeout?","date":"2020-06-21 20:28:46 +0200","categories":["ci"],"tags":["ci","travis-ci","travis"],"description":null,"keywords":"ci, travis-ci, travis","author":"Zoran Pandovski","cover":{"childImageSharp":{"fixed":{"base64":"data:image/png;base64,","width":204,"height":132,"src":"/static/196a2651664d4af8da2ae6b5dce6a2a2/02521/ci.png","srcSet":"/static/196a2651664d4af8da2ae6b5dce6a2a2/02521/ci.png 1x"}}}},"fields":{"slug":"/how-to-increase-travis-ci-timeout","date":"2020-06-21T18:28:46.000Z"}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/how-to-increase-travis-ci-timeout","nexttitle":"TypeError 'NoneType' object is not subscriptable","nextslug":"/typeerror-nonetype-object-is-not-subscriptable","prevtitle":"NaN and Infinity in Java","prevslug":"/nan-and-infinity-in-java","tagList":["python","pandas","abstraction","OOP","Class","java","collection","API","Map","HashMap","LinkedHashMap","TreeMap","Python","cli","args","argparse","javascript","es6","beginner","codenewbie","Primary_key","implementation","Composite_key","language-support","localization","internationalization","linux","file permissions","Project Euler","Algortithms","SQL","database","commands","GO","Datatypes","Variables","Constants","HTML5","Web development","tricks","NumpPy","array","NLP","libraries","text processing","go","golang","data-structu